recipes.title: Acharuli Khachapuri
recipes.description: A traditional Georgian boat-shaped bread filled with melted cheese, butter, and topped with a runny egg yolk.
recipes.instructions: Mix warm milk, sugar, yeast, and yogurt. Let it rest for 10 minutes. Add flour and salt, then knead into a soft dough. Let rise for 1 hour. Roll into a boat shape and fill with grated cheese. Bake at 220°C (425°F) for 15–20 minutes until golden. Add butter and a raw egg yolk in the center right after baking; stir it into the hot cheese before eating.

recipes.title: Kubdari
recipes.description: A Georgian meat-filled bread from the Svaneti region, known for its rich flavor and aromatic spices.
recipes.instructions: Prepare dough with flour, yeast, water, sugar, and salt; let it rise for 1 hour. Mix minced meat with onion, garlic, and spices. Roll dough into circles, place filling in the center, seal, and flatten slightly. Bake at 200°C (400°F) for 25–30 minutes until golden brown.

recipes.title: Megruli Khachapuri
recipes.description: A rich Georgian cheese bread from the Samegrelo region, filled and topped with melted cheese.
recipes.instructions: Prepare dough by mixing milk, yogurt, yeast, sugar, and flour with salt. Let it rise for 1 hour. Divide into two parts; roll one out and fill with half of the cheese. Cover with the second layer and seal the edges. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top. Bake at 220°C (425°F) for 15–20 minutes until golden and bubbly.

recipes.title: Egg Benedict
recipes.description: A classic brunch dish featuring poached eggs, crispy bacon or ham, and hollandaise sauce on toasted English muffins.
recipes.instructions: Toast muffins and cook bacon. For hollandaise, whisk egg yolks and lemon juice over simmering water, slowly adding melted butter until thick. Poach eggs in simmering water with vinegar for 3 minutes. Place bacon on muffins, top with poached eggs, and spoon hollandaise sauce over.

recipes.title: Lobio
recipes.description: A traditional Georgian bean stew, hearty and flavored with onions, herbs, and walnuts.
recipes.instructions: Soak beans overnight and cook until soft. Sauté onion and garlic, then mix with cooked beans, walnuts, and spices. Mash lightly and add vinegar and cilantro. Serve warm or cold with bread.

recipes.title: Chaqapuli
recipes.description: A Georgian spring stew made with lamb, tarragon, and sour plums, known for its fresh and tangy taste.
ingredients: 4–5 green plums or 2 tbsp tkemali sauce
recipes.instructions: Place lamb and onions in a pot, pour in wine, and cook until meat starts to soften. Add chopped herbs and plums, season with salt and pepper, and simmer for 1 hour until the meat is tender and the broth is flavorful.

recipes.title: Khinkali
recipes.description: Georgian dumplings filled with spiced meat and broth, enjoyed by hand and known for their juicy interior.
recipes.instructions: Mix flour, salt, and water into a soft dough. Combine meat with onion, spices, and broth to make a juicy filling. Roll dough thin, cut circles, add filling, and pleat into dumplings. Boil in salted water for 10–12 minutes. Serve hot with black pepper.
